    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "**Describe the solution you'd like**\r\n\r\nI think we can set up static analysis for cython code. When code quality improves, it will be easier for new people to join the development,\r\n\r\nFor example, we could use deepsource.io (There might be better choices. This is the first tool I tried, from Github market): \r\nhttps://deepsource.io/gh/Endle/cython/run/e06c2d6d-6e31-4688-8bd4-59f0a31748c6/python/\r\n\r\nThe analysis is executed in deepsource server, instead of travis ci or github action. Adding a static analysis won't delay current CI jobs.\r\n\r\nIt might be easier to integrate a github market app after [Migration to Github Action](https://github.com/cython/cython/issues/3913)\r\nHowever. I don't think Issue #3913 is a blocker to this proposal. We can start static analysis (see above) without touching current CI pipeline\r\n",
    "closed_at": null,
    "comment_data": [
